    "body" : "<p>It's called a favicon, and all you have to do is:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>If there's an icon at <code>/favicon.ico</code>, use that.</li>\n<li>Otherwise, get the content of the page, and extract the location from <code>&lt;link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"<i>URL goes here</i>\" /&gt;</code>. You’ll need to use an HTML parser and find the <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> with a <code>rel</code> of either <code>icon</code> or <code>shortcut icon</code>.</li>\n</ol>\n"
